title: 10 Foil Packet Meals for Easy Weeknight Dinners
text:
All photos 
Sriracha, rice vinegar, and soy sauce add a pop of flavor to plain salmon. Corn, broccoli, cauliflower, and grape tomatoes count toward your daily vegetable servings. The best part? Foil packet meals mean no dishes—just throw away the foil when you're done! 
Get the recipe: Sriracha Honey Salmon Photo: Running to the Kitchen Philly Cheesesteak Tin Foil Dinners 3 of 10 All photos 
You could cook this meal over the fire when you're camping in the great outdoors or you could stay home and bake it in the oven at 400°F. The delicious flavors of a Philly cheesesteak—beef, green pepper, mushrooms, and provolone cheese—are wrapped in foil for this quick meal.
